title: Classic Chicken Pasta
ingredients: chicken breast (500g),pasta (200g),tomatoes (4 pieces),42,olive oil (2 tbsp),basil leaves (handful),salt and pepper to taste
instructions: Cook pasta according to package instructions in salted water.|Season chicken with salt and pepper on both sides.|Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.|Cook chicken until golden brown, about 5-6 minutes per side.|Remove chicken and let rest, then slice into strips.|In the same pan, add minced garlic and cook for 30 seconds until fragrant.|Add diced tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes until softened.|Return chicken to pan, add cooked pasta, and toss to combine.|Garnish with fresh basil leaves and serve immediately.
author: Chef Alex

title: Creamy Tomato Soup
ingredients: tomatoes (1kg),onions (2 medium),garlic (4 cloves),vegetable broth (1 liter),heavy cream (200ml),olive oil (2 tbsp),fresh basil (5 leaves),salt and black pepper
instructions: Chop onions and mince garlic.|Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.|Sauté onions until translucent, about 5 minutes.|Add garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.|Add chopped tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.|Pour in vegetable broth and bring to a simmer.|Cook for 20 minutes until tomatoes are very soft.|Remove from heat and blend with an immersion blender until smooth.|Stir in heavy cream and season with salt and pepper.|Garnish with fresh basil leaves before serving.
author: Maria Cooks

title: Garlic Parmesan Bread
ingredients: French bread loaf (1),garlic (5 cloves),butter (100g),parmesan cheese (50g, grated),fresh parsley (2 tbsp, chopped),olive oil (1 tbsp)
instructions: Preheat oven to 200°C (400°F).|Mix softened butter with minced garlic, chopped parsley, and grated parmesan.|Slice bread without cutting through the bottom crust.|Spread garlic butter mixture generously between slices.|Drizzle with olive oil and wrap loaf in aluminum foil.|Bake for 15 minutes, then open foil and bake for 5 more minutes until golden and crispy.|Serve warm as an appetizer or side dish.
author: Bakery Master

title: Vegetable Stir Fry
ingredients: bell peppers (2, various colors),broccoli (1 head),carrots (2 medium),soy sauce (3 tbsp),fresh ginger (1 tbsp, grated),garlic (2 cloves),sesame oil (1 tbsp),vegetable oil (2 tbsp)
instructions: Chop all vegetables into bite-sized pieces.|Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.|Add minced ginger and garlic, stir for 30 seconds until fragrant.|Add carrots and broccoli, stir-fry for 3-4 minutes.|Add bell peppers and cook for 2 more minutes.|Reduce heat and pour in soy sauce, stirring to coat all vegetables.|Drizzle with sesame oil and toss to combine.|Serve immediately over rice or noodles.
author: Healthy Eats

title: Chocolate Chip Cookies
ingredients: flour (250g),butter (150g, softened),sugar (150g),chocolate chips (200g),eggs (2),vanilla extract (1 tsp),baking soda (1 tsp),salt (pinch)
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).|Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.|Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.|Stir in vanilla extract.|In a separate bowl, mix flour with baking soda and salt.|Gradually add dry ingredients to wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.|Fold in chocolate chips.|Drop spoonfuls of dough onto a baking sheet.|Bake for 10-12 minutes until edges are golden brown.|Let cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to wire rack.
author: Sweet Treats
